From: T510-AI Builder <builder@example.com>
Date: 2026-04-03
Subject: Enable spidev for LMK04828 userspace initialization

Enable CONFIG_SPI_SPIDEV=y in xilinx_zynqmp_defconfig so the board can
expose PS SPI1 as /dev/spidev1.0 for LMK04828 userspace initialization.

Signed-off-by: T510-AI Builder <builder@example.com>
---
 arch/arm64/configs/xilinx_zynqmp_defconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/configs/xilinx_zynqmp_defconfig b/arch/arm64/configs/xilinx_zynqmp_defconfig
index xxxxxxx..xxxxxxx 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/configs/xilinx_zynqmp_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm64/configs/xilinx_zynqmp_defconfig
@@ -206,6 +206,7 @@ CONFIG_I2C_XILINX=y
 CONFIG_I2C_SLAVE=y
 CONFIG_I2C_SLAVE_EEPROM=y
 CONFIG_SPI=y
+CONFIG_SPI_SPIDEV=y
 CONFIG_SPI_CADENCE=y
 CONFIG_SPI_XILINX=y
 CONFIG_SPI_ZYNQMP_GQSPI=y
-- 
2.xx.x
